üîπ POST 7 ‚Äî DATA GOVERNANCE BEFORE ANALYTICS

Before moving into the GOLD layer, I stopped to do something that often gets skipped in portfolio projects: data governance.

At this stage, the database was already populated and stable. But analytics only make sense if the semantics are correct.

What was done:

- Created a dedicated muscle group dimension
- Mapped every exercise explicitly to a muscle group
- Built an audit view to detect unmapped exercises
- Identified a real data issue: a duplicated exercise caused by a typo
- Consolidated historical data safely (no data loss, no broken FKs)
- Re-ran the mapping as a fully reproducible load

Key points:

- No silent fixes
- No masking errors in queries
- Corrections applied at the right layer (Silver)
- Referential integrity preserved at all times

Result:

- 100% of exercises mapped
- Zero unmapped records

Clean, auditable foundation for analytics

Only after this kind of groundwork does it make sense to build metrics.
Now the GOLD layer can be built on something solid ‚Äî not assumptions.

